Package com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.jpa

Class AcrossHibernateJpaModule.AcrossHibernateJpaModuleBuilder

java.lang.Object
com.foreach.across.modules.hibernate.jpa.AcrossHibernateJpaModule.AcrossHibernateJpaModuleBuilder
Enclosing class:
AcrossHibernateJpaModule
public static class AcrossHibernateJpaModule.AcrossHibernateJpaModuleBuilder extends Object
Builder for creating a custom AcrossHibernateJpaModule. If you only specify a prefix all other values will get generated defaults. Consider prefix foo:
  • module name would be FooJpaModule
  • properties would be prefixed with foo.jpa
  • datasource bean with name fooDataSource would be looked for
  • created beans would be exposed with a foo prefix, fi the transaction manager bean would be accessible as fooJpaTransactionManager
